74
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:11,860
I'll go check.

75
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:13,152
I'll go with you.

76
00:05:15,872 --> 00:05:16,699
Don't hit me!

77
00:05:16,819 --> 00:05:19,100
Senior, I didn't mean to.

78
00:05:19,100 --> 00:05:19,500
Stop!

79
00:05:23,139 --> 00:05:23,660
Wanyan.

80
00:05:23,860 --> 00:05:24,579
What's wrong?

81
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:25,459
Master.

82
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:28,459
I was just teaching her a lesson.

83
00:05:28,779 --> 00:05:30,339
Who knew she's this fragile?

84
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:36,959
Are you okay?

85
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,079
Xiaoying.

86
00:05:41,279 --> 00:05:42,720
I didn't mean to.

87
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:45,060
Wanyan,

88
00:05:45,819 --> 00:05:47,259
why did you hurt Rourou so badly?

89
00:05:49,779 --> 00:05:52,379
How imposing you are when angry!

90
00:05:52,819 --> 00:05:53,860
Listen.

91
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,879
She deliberately fell on me

92
00:05:56,279 --> 00:05:57,560
and stained my dress.

93
00:05:58,459 --> 00:05:59,379
This dress

94
00:05:59,540 --> 00:06:01,220
is one of a kind in the Nine Heavens.

95
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,540
She can't compensate it.

96
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:07,899
I just gave her a minor punishment

97
00:06:08,139 --> 00:06:09,540
as a warning.

98
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:11,959
As expected,

99
00:06:13,860 --> 00:06:14,980
low-ranked disciples

100
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:18,259
are worthless in your eyes.

101
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:25,560
The Nine Heavens

102
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,959
isn't worth staying for.

103
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,199
Rourou,

104
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:32,779
leave with me.

105
00:06:34,336 --> 00:06:35,104
Okay.

106
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:36,759
Stop!

107
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:37,540
Stop now!

108
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:38,379
Think you can leave?

109
00:06:38,379 --> 00:06:38,779
Wanyan.

110
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:46,660
You can't stop them.

111
00:06:47,139 --> 00:06:48,180
Don't embarrass yourself.

112
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,600
Just let her go.

113
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:11,600
This is...

114
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,560
This is

115
00:07:17,899 --> 00:07:19,540
where he and I lived.

116
00:07:25,819 --> 00:07:27,220
(This was our home.)

117
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,000
(You're gone.)

118
00:07:30,279 --> 00:07:31,939
(I'll wait for you instead.)

119
00:07:33,459 --> 00:07:35,019
(Maybe after 300 years,)

120
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:37,639
(you'll return like I did.)

121
00:08:19,540 --> 00:08:21,740
(This is the only thing
my mother left me.)

122
00:08:22,899 --> 00:08:24,060
When scared,

123
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:25,819
I feel her watching over me.

124
00:08:26,939 --> 00:08:28,060
I want you to have it.

125
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:28,939
This way,

126
00:08:29,379 --> 00:08:30,660
even when I'm gone,

127
00:08:30,899 --> 00:08:32,100
it'll keep you safe.

128
00:08:39,899 --> 00:08:40,820
(Take this figurine.)

129
00:08:41,179 --> 00:08:42,460
(Consider this a memento of me.)

130
00:08:43,980 --> 00:08:46,500
If my time runs short,

131
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:49,299
I'll allow you

132
00:08:49,700 --> 00:08:50,785
to love someone else later.

133
00:09:05,299 --> 00:09:06,496
- She's out.
- She's out.

134
00:09:06,496 --> 00:09:07,648
She is War God, right?

135
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:15,120
Are you the heroine
who killed the Night Deity?

136
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,120
Why are you here?

137
00:09:18,259 --> 00:09:20,659
The Night Deity destroyed our homes.

138
00:09:21,019 --> 00:09:22,259
Our families perished,

139
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:24,460
and we became refugees,

140
00:09:24,779 --> 00:09:26,820
so we had to survive by begging.

141
00:09:27,259 --> 00:09:29,820
We had no idea how to go on living

142
00:09:30,179 --> 00:09:32,580
until you slew the Night Deity.

143
00:09:33,179 --> 00:09:36,019
Please take pity on us.

144
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,620
Grant us a shelter,

145
00:09:37,940 --> 00:09:39,179
so that we can live on.

146
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:40,419
I'm begging you.

147
00:09:41,059 --> 00:09:42,500
- I'm begging you.
- I'm begging you.

148
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,340
War God. I'm begging you.

149
00:09:47,779 --> 00:09:49,419
If you truly have nowhere else,

150
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:50,620
you may stay here.

151
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:53,100
But you must sustain yourselves.

152
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:55,259
Thank you for sheltering us.

153
00:09:55,419 --> 00:09:56,139
Thank you.

154
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:58,340
We finally have a home.

155
00:09:58,539 --> 00:10:00,860
We won't be afraid
of being bullied by others.

156
00:10:00,940 --> 00:10:02,100
Thank War God now!

157
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:03,240
Thank War God now!

158
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,940
No need.

159
00:10:05,299 --> 00:10:07,039
Please rise. No need for this.

160
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,960
Thank you, War God.

161
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,480
Let's go.

162
00:10:10,559 --> 00:10:11,860
- Thank you, War God.
- Hurry.

163
00:10:14,899 --> 00:10:15,659
Thank you, War God.

164
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:16,740
Thank you, War God.

165
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:28,980
What's wrong?

166
00:10:30,259 --> 00:10:31,259
Why don't you go in?

167
00:10:32,779 --> 00:10:33,440
Miss.

168
00:10:34,019 --> 00:10:35,360
Are you an immortal?

169
00:10:38,860 --> 00:10:40,059
I'm just an ordinary person,

170
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:41,080
like all of you.

171
00:10:41,580 --> 00:10:43,940
Then why would you

172
00:10:44,059 --> 00:10:47,019
take in homeless people like us?

173
00:10:50,279 --> 00:10:52,960
Because a man once taught me to do so.

174
00:10:55,539 --> 00:10:57,820
I want to become like you.

175
00:10:58,940 --> 00:11:01,259
Okay. You will someday.

176
00:11:01,820 --> 00:11:03,019
I swear

177
00:11:03,379 --> 00:11:05,340
that I'll protect our home for you!

178
00:11:05,620 --> 00:11:06,100
Okay.

179
00:11:06,779 --> 00:11:07,220
Good child.

180
00:11:07,940 --> 00:11:08,539
Let's go in.

181
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:09,259
Hmm.

182
00:11:13,524 --> 00:11:16,352
